    job_description:
      "Job Number: 35498\n\nPosition Title: Principal Online Marketing Specialist\n\nExternal Description\n\nJob Description\n\nReporting to the Group Vice President - Marketing, As the Web Visual and UX Designer, you'll be responsible for shaping the design system for our corporate website experience, and continually optimize audience-centric paths to deepen engagement and increase site conversion. The Web Visual and UX Designer will collaborate with our branding and web development teams to develop plans and initiatives to enhance the website's user experience across their entire web interaction, whether they are a first-time visitor, repeat visitor or existing customer. This is the role for you if you're passionate about how data informs design and user experience principles to create a cohesive and connected digital experience, tailored to an array of visitor profiles.\n\nWhat You'll Do\n• Develop a captivating and cohesive design experience for our corporate global and localized websites, that delights and excites customers\n• Conduct user research, and deliver best practices in User-Centered (UCD), information architecture, and interaction design, tailored to serve multiple segments\n• Evolve a design system that elevates our brand and supports demand generation; provide design and UX input to our web CMS component library, ensuring design consistency, accessibility, and reusability\n• Develop wireframes, page designs, and prototypes to support web, landing pages, interactive components and owned properties\n• Work closely with web developers and web content merchandising colleagues to design, build, and deploy experiments targeted to collecting feedback on user behavior, and use that information to further optimize the website design and user experience\n\nKey Essentials\n• Bachelor's degree in design or related discipline. Master's degree preferred.\n• 10+ years experience in digital and website design, building and leveraging industry best practices for b2b digital demand generation\n• Demonstrated experience developing design guidelines and specifications, and in managing on-going governance to ensure consistency\n• A portfolio that demonstrates your design talent creating user-centered design solutions (flows, prototypes, wireframes) and solid visual designs (mockups and style guides)\n• Demonstrated proficiency with Adobe Creative Suite, Sketch and InVision with experience in building and maintaining a pattern library or design systems\n• Demonstrated history of acquiring user data (e.g., conducting usability studies, performing user research) and creating user flows, tailored to personas and their buying paths\n\nWhat Does Success Look Like?\n• Strong, technical, communication, collaboration, and leadership skills\n• Methodical, metrics-driven approach to continuous improvement with the ability to put insights into design and user flow action\n• Demonstrated ability to think strategically and execute effectively with a strong solutions and results orientation\n• Passion for innovation, experimentation and reinvention\n• Program management and design that results in a recognized, modern B2B website that effectively reflects Informatica's leadership and branding, delivers personalized customer experiences, and drives web-to-lead growth.\n\nNice to Have\n• Hands-on experience with Adobe Experience Manager or similar web content management systems, Adobe Target, Adobe Audience ManagerPerks & Benefits\n• Comprehensive health, vision, and wellness benefits (Paid parental leave, adoption benefits, life insurance, disability insurance and 401k plan or international pension/retirement plans\n• Flexible time-off policy and hybrid working practices\n• Tuition reimbursement program to support your and personal growth\n• Equity opportunities and an employee stock purchase program (ESPP)\n• Comprehensive Mental Health and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) benefit\n\nWe're guided by our DATA values and we are passionate about building and delivering solutions that accelerate data innovations. At Informatica, we know diversity drives innovation. We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer dedicated to maintaining a work environment free from discrimination, one where all employees are treated with dignity.\n\nInformatica (NYSE: INFA), an Enterprise Cloud Data Management leader, brings data to life by empowering businesses to realize the transformative power of their most critical assets. We have pioneered the Informatica Intelligent Data Management Cloud™ (IDMC) that manages data across any multi-cloud, hybrid system, democratizing data to advance business strategies. Customers in over 100 countries and 85 of the Fortune 100 rely on Informatica. www.informatica.com. Connect with LinkedIn, Twitter, and Facebook. Informatica. Where data comes to life.\n\nInformatica we know diversity drives innovation. We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer dedicated to maintaining a work environment free from discrimination, one where all employees are treated with dignity and respect. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, gender, sex, sexual orientation, marital status, religion, age, disability, gender identity, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by applicable law and Informatica policy.\n\nCity: City\n\nState\n\nSeniority Level: Mid-Senior Level\n\nAlternative Location(s) :\n\nCommunity / Marketing Title: Web Visual and UX Designer\n\nRemote LinkedIn Hashtag\n\nCompany Profile\n\nEEO Employer Verbiage:\n\nAt Informatica we know diversity drives innovation. We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer dedicated to maintaining a work environment free from discrimination, one where all employees are treated with dignity and respect. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, gender, sex, sexual orientation, marital status, religion, age, disability, gender identity, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by applicable law and Informatica policy.\n\nTravel Requirement: Limited",
